<p>I need to parse some markup similar to this one, from an html page:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;a href="#"&gt;   &lt;i class="icon-location"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;London &lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I need to get <strong>London</strong>.</p>  <p>I did try something like (using <code>cheerio</code>):</p>  <pre><code>$('a', 'i[class="icon-location"]').text(); </code></pre>  <p>or</p>  <pre><code>$('a &gt; i[class="icon-location"]').text(); </code></pre>  <p>without success...</p>  <p>I'd like to avoid methods like <code>next()</code>, since the expression should be passed to a method which just extracts the text from the selector.</p>  <p>What expression should I use (if it's feasible) ?</p>